<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 07 at 2:43PM EDT  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS POSSIBLE THIS AFTERNOON...
Scattered showers and thunderstorms will move across portions of
southeast South Carolina this afternoon. These storms will be
capable of producing gusty winds and hail up to the size of
pennies. A few stronger storms will be possible, and could
produce hail up to the size of quarters and necessitate the
issuance of Severe Thunderstorm Warnings. Thunderstorm activity
should diminish by the late afternoon hours.</description>
<instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards or the Internet for
the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
